 and background by staining the roots, and (ii) avoid overlapping roots by not exceeding a RLD of 1 cm cm {\`{A}}2 . Under these conditions, good length estimates can be obtained with WinRHIZO TM (global thresholding + pixel reclassification). The Kimura method in IJ{\_}Rhizo can be an alternative to WinRHIZO TM .},
