366 mm of water for evaporation. Planted mesocoms retained on average 40{\%} (i.e. 506 mm) of the rainfall that could be used for evapotranspiration. Wash-out of solids from the bare substrate amounted to 394 g m−2, but was not significantly higher than the loss of substrate from planted mesocosms. Under the extreme climatic conditions in present study, plant mixtures were not superior to monocultures in terms of cooling potentials, water retention and wash-out, but plant survivorship and maintenance of a high vegetation cover proved to be the main drivers of these services.},
