(1) alpha trait - species trait values relative to co-occuring species
(2) beta trait - average trait value in communities where species occur
(3) 'a first B throughout' hypothesi: alpha niche comes before beta niche (sorted by environment) --{\textgreater} phylogenetic signal within-communities
(4) hierarcial diversification hypothesis: colonization of different habitats precedes alpha niche --{\textgreater} phylogenetic signal in traits of taxa living in different habitats, but not traits of co-occurring taxa

Findings:
