ght drive environmental effect of plant diversity on decomposition in our plant communities, but this remains to be tested.4.Synthesis. Our results demonstrate that both substrate quality and soil environment contribute to the net negative effect of plant diversity on root decomposition. This study promotes our mechanistic understanding of increased soil carbon accumulation in more diverse grassland plant communities.This article is protected by copyright. All rights reserved.},
