um. In contrast to leaves, trees are not constrained in the way they construct fine roots: plants can construct high or low SRL roots of any tissue density. High RTD is the most consistent below- ground trait that reflects adaptation to infertile soil. Key-words: determinants of plant community diversity and structure, leaf economic spectrum, plant economic spectrum, root branching, root diameter, root economic spectrum, root tissue density, soil fertility, specific root length, wood economic spectrum Introdu},
